    <prj:ScienceGoal>
        <prj:name>CO(2-1) mapping of NGC 1365</prj:name>
        <prj:note>Giant Molecular Clouds (GMCs) are a preferred way in which the molecular gas organizes itself and represent the seeds of Galactic star formation. However only recently we acquired the essential instrumentation power to access their properties in galaxies that actually dominate the star formation budget of the universe. The PdBI Arcsecond Whirlpool Survey (PAWS) of the inner 8 kpc of M51 has challenged some common beliefs about GMCs, in particular the properties, formation and evolution of clouds in M51 appear tantalizing function of environments and specifically of large scale dynamical effects. Taking full advantage of the ALMA capabilities, here we propose to further broaden our knowledge about the effect of the dynamics and stellar feedback on the molecular gas at cloud scale (i.e. 45 pc and 10^5 Mo) by mapping the full extension of NGC 1365 bar. This observation will be critical to shed new light on the connections between kpc and pc scale phenomena and on the mechanisms that determines the different modalities in which stars born.</prj:note>
