    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>The molecular gas organizes itself preferentially in Giant Molecular Clouds (GMCs) that contain most seeds for massive Galactic star formation. However, only now it has become possible to study their properties in massive disk galaxies that actually dominate the star formation budget of the universe. The PdBI Arcsecond Whirlpool Survey (PAWS) of the inner 8 kpc of M51 has challenged some common beliefs about GMCs. Particularly the properties, formation and evolution of clouds in M51 appear to be a tantalizing function of environment, or more specific, of large-scale dynamical effects. Taking full advantage of ALMA's unique capabilities, we propose to map the full stellar bar in NGC 1365 in CO(2-1) for an in-depth study of the largely unconstrainted effect of bar dynamics on the molecular gas at cloud scale  resolution (i.e. 45 pc and 10^5 Mo).  These observation are critical to reveal the connection between kpc- and pc-scale phenomena and the mechanisms that determine the different mode in which stars sem to be born.</prp:abstract>
